33.282.В В Tax expenditure budget, content, submitted when вҖ” cost вҖ” benefit analysis, contents вҖ” department reports on tax credits, exemptions, deductions or preferences, failure to file. вҖ” 1.В В Subject to appropriation the office of administration shall develop a tax expenditure budget for submission to the general assembly in conjunction with the submission of the state budget as required in section 33.280.В В The tax expenditure budget shall indicate, on an annual basis, the reduction in revenue collections for each fiscal year as a result of each deduction, exemption, credit or other tax preference as may be authorized by law, and shall indicate, where appropriate, the tax source of each state-funded program.В В Periodically the tax expenditure budget shall include a cost-benefit analysis of the following:
вҖғВ (1)В В The neighborhood assistance program, sections 32.100 to 32.125;
вҖғВ (2)В В Tax increment financing, sections 99.800 to 99.865;
вҖғВ (3)В В Export and infrastructure funding, sections 100.250 to 100.297;
вҖғВ (4)В В Credit for new expanded business facility, sections 135.100 to 135.150;
вҖғВ (5)В В Enterprise zones, sections 135.200 to 135.256;
вҖғВ (6)В В Main street program, sections 251.470 to 251.485;
вҖғВ (7)В В Economic development districts, sections 251.500 to 251.510;
вҖғВ (8)В В Rural economic development, sections 620.155 to 620.165;
вҖғВ (9)В В Export development, sections 620.170 to 620.174;
вҖғВ (10)В В Small business incubator program, section 620.495; and
вҖғВ (11)В В Other programs as may be practical.В В ВӯВӯВӯ
вҖғВ 2.В В On or before October first of each year each state department authorized by law to offer deductions, exemptions, credits or other tax preferences shall submit to the budget director the estimated amount of such tax expenditures for the fiscal year beginning July first of the following year and a cost/benefit analysis of such tax expenditures for the preceding fiscal year.В В Such estimates and analysis shall be in the manner and form prescribed by the budget director and shall be submitted by the budget director to the chairman of the senate appropriations committee and the chairman of the house budget committee by January first of each year.
вҖғВ 3.В В No new tax credits, except the senior citizens property tax credit as referenced in chapter 135, shall be issued or certified for any tax year beginning after July first of the following year unless the estimate of such credits have been reviewed and approved by a majority of the senate appropriations committee and the house budget committee.
(L. 1988 H.B. 1054, et al. В§ 2, A.L. 1993 H.B. 566, A.L. 1995 H.B. 414)
